meter space which fully contains the observed values. Exploiting the\nincreasing number of high-energy cut-offs quoted in the literature, we report\non the comparison of physical quantities obtained using MoCA with those\nestimated using commonly adopted spectral Comptonisation models. Finally, we\ndiscuss the negligible impact of different black hole masses and accretion\nrates on the inferred relations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Aug 2019 18:00:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-09"}
